definition.value: A mistaken belief or a wrong idea pertaining to Japanese persons or persons with Japanese heritage.
A mistaken belief or a wrong idea pertaining to sexuality.
Sexual arousal by breastfeeding on a person's breast.
Urination which is uncontrolled.
A medical symptom primarily affecting the urinary system.

Symptoms that result from pathologic processes affecting the urinary bladder and/or urethra. They include urinary frequency and urgency, dysuria, nocturia, incomplete voiding, and poor stream during urination.
Involuntary passage of urine outside the body.
Urinary leakage that occurs during either penetration or orgasm and can occur with a sexual partner or with masturbation.
Urinary incontinence at the moment of sexual climax (orgasm).
A device which records data about a patient.
A patient data recorder which produces graphical output.
A device utilized for plethysmography.
A device utilized for photoplethysmography.

A small clear acrylic device that contains a light source, and a light detector. The light source illuminates the capillary bed of the clitoral tissue and the blood circulating within it. As clitoral engorgement increases, more light is reflected into the photosensitive cell of the device. The clitoral photoplethysmograph is placed by the participant between the labia minora; the light detector is oriented toward the clitoris. It can be attached to a vaginal photoplethysmograph so that both CBV and vaginal pulse amplitude (VPA) can be measured simultaneously.
A device utilized for vaginal photoplethysmography.
A device utilized for penile photoplethysmography.
A measurement of any physiological phenomenon.
Recording of change in the size of a part as modified by the circulation in it.

Plethysmographic determination in which the intensity of light reflected from the skin surface and the red cells below is measured to determine the blood volume of the respective area. There are two types, transmission and reflectance.
Measurement of clitoral blood volume (CBV) using a direct current signal.
A technique using light to measure the amount of blood in the walls of the vagina.
A measurement of bloodflow to the penis which involves a device which emits and detects that is mounted on the patient's penis.
Measurement of bloodflow to the penis, typically used as a proxy for measurement of sexual arousal.
A measurement of bloodflow to the penis which involves placing the patient's penis into a container to measure volume.
Measurement of bloodflow to the vagina, typically used as a proxy for measurement of sexual arousal.
Discrimination based on medical diagnoses, diseases, disorders, etc.
Discrimination based on HIV status.

Human sexual behavior between family members or close relatives. This typically includes sexual activity between people in consanguinity (blood relations), and sometimes those related by affinity (marriage or stepfamily), adoption, clan, or lineage.
The mating of plants or non-human animals which are closely related genetically.
Incestuous behavior which is abusive in nature, i.e. without the consent of involved persons or against their will (such as a parent with a young child).
Incestuous behavior between two siblings.
A form of child sexual abuse in which a prepubescent child is sexually abused by one or more other children or adolescents, and in which no adult is directly involved.
Incestuous behavior between a parent and a child.
Incestuous behavior toward a child which is abusive in nature, i.e. without the consent of involved persons or against their will.
Incestuous behavior between an adult and a child.
Incestuous behavior between a stepparent and their stepchild.
Incestuous behavior which is considered homosexual in nature (i.e. between two men or between a man and a boy).
Incestuous behavior which is considered heterosexual in nature (i.e. between a woman and a boy or between a man and a girl).
Incestuous behavior between two adults.
Incestuous behavior between an aunt or uncle (gender-neutral word: pibling) and their niece or nephew (gender-neutral word: niefling).
Incestuous behavior between two cousins.
Incestuous behavior between two twins (either monozygotic or dizygotic).
Sexual activity or marriage between persons who were unaware of a family relationship between them which would be considered incestuous.

A genre of pornography involving the depiction of incest (sexual activity between relatives). Incest pornography can feature actual relatives, but the main type of this pornography is fauxcest, which features non-related actors of similar looks to suggest family relationship.
A loosely defined community of LGBTQIA+ persons who practice BDSM activities.
A loosely defined community of gay men who practice BDSM activities.
A loosely defined community of lesbians who practice BDSM activities.
A loosely defined community of transgender people who practice BDSM activities.
A practice of dominance and submission, where a submissive will give gifts and money to a financial dominant.
Flags used by or used to represent members of the sexuality or sexuality-based community.
